metadata.name: In the Edge #459
metadata.description:
./ In the Edge

It's been a long time since your journey began, caring for the ones you love, pursuing your dreams, and giving the best of you. 

Now you know you can't go back, you can't go further, you know your time is coming.

How far did you go? It doesn't matter, you did it right. Your accomplishments will serve well the next generations in their journeys, in their search for themselves.

Now it's time to stop, time to take a moment and contemplate the vast universe.

Soon all of this will be ending.

You did it right.

Embrace the void.
=========
=========


./ Color scheme (feature)
There are 12 color schemes and with each set, specific arrays for color collections for the space, stars, planet, and accent colors. 

These are color schemes in the known universe of "In the Edge":
- Mars visions
- Cyberpunk
- Unknown passenger 
- Renegade
- Primary
- Coral
- r.e.d.
- Machines of an ancient-future 
- The void
- Tinted light 
- Malibu dreams
- Atari (horrendous brown, red and yellowish combinations... I love it)

./ Mountain type (feature)
In the Edge, you will find a mountain, and that mountain will be special, which type will you find?

- Parallela insolitum
- Sandy dunes of the truth
- Wavy uncertainty
- Intrinsic soul ridges
- Cerritulus formationis

./ Mountain direction (feature)
Life is about direction... mountains too.

- Left
- Right
- Left-Right

./ Space scenery
This is the spicy touch, some of the iterations will have animation and others will not, giving you a clear view of the magnificent space in front of you.

- Clean (NOT animated)
- Windy planet (animated)
- Topographic planet (animated)
- Meteor shower (animated)

./ Distance from Earth (feature)
How far did you go? Your travel could be from 1 lightyear to 999,999,999 lightyears (that's a lot of lights and years!). However just a few will pass the barrier of 99,999,999ly.

// Additional perks
./ Planet names 
Planet names are unique and they are conformed by three blocks.

The first block is a conjunction between ancient Latin names and Japanese last names. 

The second block takes the last three characters from the fxhash.

The third block takes three numbers from the number seed obtained from fxrand().

The planet you land will be unique, as unique as you are.

// Controls
./ Pause-Play animation
Because maybe (and just maybe) you want to freeze the perfect moment before closing your eyes.

[Backspace] Pause.
[Enter] Play

Applies to "Space scenery" features windy planet, topographic planet, and meteor shower.

metadata.name: Euphonic #1197
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.

metadata.name: Memo #237
metadata.description:
Memo is a abstract expression of memories written on small pieces of paper, pictures of important moments or a reminder of all the things You have forgotten.

Memo is created with P5JS. Large number of rectangles are packed in loops to the canvas with a random rectangle packing algorithm with simple collision detection. 
The looped area varies from 1 vertical or horizontal rectangle to 8x8 grid. Packed area is created with simple random walking grid loop.
60+ color palettes are handpicked and they can appear reversed. 
One random palette is picked for each piece and p5js.noise() drives the colors, size and angle on the rects with lots of attributes.

Click 'n' to add white noise.
Click 's' to save image as jpeg.

Click '1' to 1x pixelDensity(3600 x 6400 or 6400 x 3600 px - default).
Click '2' to 2x pixelDensity(7200 x 12800 or 12800 x 7200 px).

VGA 2022 / CC BY-NC 4.0

metadata.name: Ornithic #184
metadata.description:
Pure p5.js code. No svg, no image, no other materials. Creating code arts with polar coordinate system and algorithms are my passion. This generative art contains a lot of features that may be rare than common.  

• 30 color palettes // 2 of them have 3 different colors
• 4 grass structures // With the same algorithm 
• 16 flower types //  Count, leaf number and size
• 6 color functions // Different colorizations with b&w 

Also, the outputs of the project are very high resolution to print or something like that.
April / 2022
Rhaegar

metadata.name: On the sea, I ... #78
metadata.description:
Generative painting based on churning waves with floating buoys. Represented in three different media.

Features:
- Three drawing styles: "watercolor" 70%, "brush" 30%, or "block" 70%
- Warm white or blue waves
- Variable border and column sizes
- Number of columns
- Calm waves at the edges or center
- Color 80% or red 20% buoys
- Buoy drawing style, "watercolor" or "brush"

Viewing in desktop Chrome is recommended for the best results.
Press ’s’ to save a screenshot. Image size is 928x1200px
Press ’p’ to pause/resume.

Add '&size=#' to the end of the live view URL to render a variation of your edition at a resolution up to 3,000 px.

metadata.name: Omega Point #53
metadata.description:
In the collapsing universe approaching singularity, the last remaining cybernetic organisms encounter the state of infinite knowledge, information, and computational resources.
Although the living creatures in the Omega Point are destined for imminent destruction, they experience infinite life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'space' - improve image quality
'f' - increase rendering speed

The image quality gradually improves over time, up to a certain level. To reach the maximum quality, press 'space'.
The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.
Requires WebGL2.

metadata.name: Emergence #44
metadata.description: This project was supposed to be released in a global one containing also my previous one Rupture. However, even if they were close in the intent by achieving some interesting pattern through a very sensitive balance between numerous parameters, they have resulted in output that can clearly appeal to different sensitivities. Then, I have prefered to separate them (and it was a bit easier to deal with the code ^^).

metadata.name: Collapsing the Wave Function #4
metadata.description:
In quantum mechanics the wave function will not collapse into one of it's potential states until it is "observed". In a similar way generative art has a ton of potential outputs until it is minted and then it "collapses" into one of those potential outputs to produce something new and unique. This is a series of art generated from different trigonometric functions. There are 8 different potential color palettes and 12 different potential functions that will produce various different patterns depending on the starting state. This project is best enjoyed in full screen mode. Hope you enjoy!

Created with p5js.

The Bearded Coder
